msItem.title: A collection of hymns, for the most part composed by Israel Najara.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 22; written lines: 22; Non-uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Catchwords on every verso. Titles and inital words in larger, frequently square characters. Pen and ink decorated initial letters and titles, e.g. folio 87r-87v.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental semi-cursive script of the 17th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Israel Najara. Sheerith Yisrael. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,206.'

history.provenance: Ya῾aḳov Eliyahu ben Daṿid Hayim Reḳaḥ

Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 321: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum: inscribed, folio [213v] (fse004v).
